🎯 PHASE 2 ROADMAP (What To Do Now)

We’ll break this into 4 layers:

Agent Specialization

Router Intelligence

Capability Registry

Stability & Clean Architecture

✅ 1️⃣ Agent Specialization (Highest Priority)
🔲 Create Separate Agents:

repo_overview_agent

architecture_agent

structure_agent

(optional) review_agent

Each should:

Have its own prompt file

Have a very narrow responsibility

Return clearly distinct output formats

Goal:
No overlap in responsibilities.

🔲 Rewrite Prompts To Be Strict

Example:

Overview agent:

Only high-level purpose

No execution flow

No deep architecture

Architecture agent:

No general summary

Only system design

Explicit component interactions

Explicit data flow

Make outputs feel different.

✅ 2️⃣ Implement Sub-Router (Inside Repo Analyzer)
🔲 Create repo_analyzer_router

It should:

Read user query

Match against capability descriptions

Route to correct sub-agent

Start with keyword-based routing.
Later upgrade to LLM-based routing.

🔲 Add Agent Registry

Create a simple metadata structure:

Agent name

Responsibility

Tool access list

Router reads this metadata only.
No internal coupling.

✅ 3️⃣ Clean Up Graph Structure

Update LangGraph to:

Main Router
 ├── Code Explainer
 └── Repo Analyzer Router
        ├── Overview
        ├── Architecture
        ├── Structure

Make sure:

State remains minimal

Each node only modifies final_answer

No unnecessary state pollution